Tech - node.js, mySql, docker, redis, bullQ, twilio

Database schemas - user, phone, email

tasks overview - 
1. register a user to the application
2. after registration add a job to the queue to generate a random number 
3. store that random number in the database in user schema after job has been processed
4. create associations of user with phone and email. (user schema should not contain ph number or email, email needs to be in email schema and number in phone schema )
5. login api that returns the token needs to be authorised with OTP, store OTP for 3 min in redis, after OTP has been verified only then return the token in api response
6. create a public api to show all users ranking based on the random number generated

